.TH LUAI 1 "June 2026" "luainstaller v1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
luai, luainstaller \- package Lua projects into same-environment executables

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B luai
.BR \-h
.br
.B luai
.BR \-v
.br
.B luai
.BR \-a " " \fIentry.lua\fR
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B luai
.BR \-t " " \fIentry.lua\fR
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B luai
.BR \-b " " \fIentry.lua\fR
.RI [ options ]
.PP
.B luainstaller
.BR help
.br
.B luainstaller
.BR version
.br
.B luainstaller
.BR analyze " " \fIentry.lua\fR
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B luainstaller
.BR trace " " \fIentry.lua\fR
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B luainstaller
.BR build " " \fIentry.lua\fR
.RI [ options ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B luainstaller
analyzes Lua dependencies and packages Lua projects into same-environment
executables. The installed package provides two command names with different
command-line personalities.
.PP
.B luai
is compact, traditional, plain, and script-friendly.
.B luainstaller
uses full subcommands and modern human-oriented output.
.PP
The compatibility promise for generated bundles is same OS, same architecture,
same ABI, and same Lua ABI. General cross-platform output and automatic
external shared-library closure are outside the current support boundary.

.SH COMMAND SPLIT
.TP
.B luai
Accepts compact commands only:
.BR \-h ,
.BR \-v ,
.BR \-a ,
.BR \-t ,
and
.BR \-b .
.TP
.B luainstaller
Accepts full subcommands only:
.BR help ,
.BR version ,
.BR analyze ,
.BR trace ,
.BR build ,
.BR logs ,
and
.BR engines .
.PP
For example,
.B luai \-b
is valid and
.B luainstaller build
is valid.
.B luai build
and
.B luainstaller \-b
are intentionally invalid.

.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Compact CLI
.nf
luai -h
luai -v
luai -a test/runtime_bundle/main.lua --max-deps 120
luai -t test/runtime_bundle/main.lua --max-deps 120
luai -b --dir test/runtime_bundle/main.lua -o build/runtime
luai -b --file test/runtime_bundle/main.lua -o build/runtime-onefile
.fi

.SS Modern CLI
.nf
luainstaller help
luainstaller version
luainstaller analyze test/runtime_bundle/main.lua --max-deps 120
luainstaller trace test/runtime_bundle/main.lua --max-deps 120
luainstaller build --dir test/runtime_bundle/main.lua -o build/runtime
luainstaller build --file test/runtime_bundle/main.lua -o build/runtime-onefile
.fi

.SH OPTIONS
The following options apply to dependency actions and build actions where
meaningful.
.TP
.BI \-o ", " \-\-out " " path
Output path for build actions.
.TP
.B \-\-dir ", " \-\-onedir
Build a directory bundle. This is the default build mode.
.TP
.B \-\-file ", " \-\-onefile
Build a self-extracting onefile bundle.
.TP
.BI \-\-include " " path
Include an additional file. May be repeated.
.TP
.BI \-\-exclude " " path
Exclude a dependency by path or basename. May be repeated.
.TP
.BI \-\-target\-os " " os
Select the target profile: linux, macos, or windows.
.TP
.BI \-\-lua\-prefix " " path
Lua prefix used by targets that require explicit headers or runtime files.
.TP
.BI \-r ", " \-\-require\-engine " " engine
Select dependency discovery: static, manual, or runtime.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-depscan
Disable automatic dependency scanning and use manual dependencies only.
.TP
.BI \-\-max\-deps " " n
Maximum dependency count.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Show more detail.

.SH OUTPUT
.B luai
uses plain, compact, line-oriented output and never emits color or animation.
.PP
.B luainstaller
uses sectioned, modern output. ANSI color and progress animation are
presentation features and are disabled for non-interactive fallback,
.B NO_COLOR ,
and CI-style output.

.SH INSTALLATION
.nf
luarocks install luainstaller
.fi
.PP
Source checkout installation:
.nf
sh tools/install-source.sh --prefix "$HOME/.local"
export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"
luai -h
luainstaller version
.fi

.SH LUA API
The CLI split does not change the Lua API.
.nf
local luainstaller = require("luainstaller")
local result = luainstaller.analyze({
  entry = "test/runtime_bundle/main.lua",
})
.fi

